ng ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":1,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":10,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":21,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":23,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":37,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":39,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Wyther was born in 1548, in Woolpit, Suffolk, England. He married Margaret Nash in 1571, in Woolpit, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died on 1 January 1596, in his hometown, at the age of 48, and was buried in Woolpit, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1548–1 January 1596":"1548–1. jaanuar 1596","1552–1615":"1552–1615","1565–1565":"1565–1565","1574–1652":"1574–1652","1577–Male":"1577–Surnud","1548–1596":"1548–1596","13 January 1574":"13. jaanuar 1574","19 August 1565":"19. august 1565","1571":"1571","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1577":"1577","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1652":"1652","1585":"1585","1596":"1596","1574":"1574","1552":"1552","1 January 1596":"1. jaanuar 1596","1549":"1549","1615":"1615","1548":"1548","Woolpit, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Woolpit, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woolpit, Suffolk, England":"Woolpit, Suffolk, England","Woolpit, Suffolk":"Woolpit, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woolpit, Mid Suffolk, Suffolk, England":"Woolpit, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1548–1 January 1596":"1548–1. tammikuuta 1596","1552–1615":"1552–1615","1565–1565":"1565–1565","1574–1652":"1574–1652","1577–Male":"1577–Kuollut","1548–1596":"1548–1596","13 January 1574":"13. tammikuuta 1574","19 August 1565":"19. elokuuta 1565","1571":"1571","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1577":"1577","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1652":"1652","1585":"1585","1596":"1596","1574":"1574","1552":"1552","1 January 1596":"1. tammikuuta 1596","1549":"1549","1615":"1615","1548":